# ResumAI

AI-powered ATS Resume Analyzer

## Tech Stack

- React + Vite (Vercel)
- Node.js + Express (Render)
- MongoDB
- AWS S3
- Groq AI

## Local setup

### Server

```bash
cd server
npm install
cp .env.example .env
# Fill MONGO_URL, JWT_SECRET, GROQ_API_KEY, AWS_*, CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:5173
npm run dev
```

### Client

```bash
cd client
npm install
cp .env.example .env
# VITE_API_URL=/api
npm run dev
```

## Production deployment

### 1. Render (backend)

- Deploy `server/` folder
- Set env vars from `server/.env.example`
- **`CLIENT_URL`** = `https://ai-resume-analysis-wheat.vercel.app` (your Vercel URL, no trailing slash)
- Health check: open `https://YOUR-SERVICE.onrender.com` → should show API running message

### 2. Vercel (frontend)

**Environment variable (required):**

| Name | Value |
|------|--------|
| `VITE_API_URL` | `https://YOUR-SERVICE.onrender.com/api` |

Example:

```
VITE_API_URL=https://ai-resume-analysis.onrender.com/api
```

Then **redeploy** (env vars are baked in at build time).

### 3. CORS

Backend allows:

- `http://localhost:5173` (local)
- `https://ai-resume-analysis-wheat.vercel.app` (production)
- `CLIENT_URL` from env

### Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| "Cannot reach the server" | Set `VITE_API_URL` on Vercel → **redeploy** (Vite bakes env at build time). Open Render URL in browser first to wake the service. |
| "Route not found" | `VITE_API_URL` must end with `/api`. Wrong: `https://xxx.onrender.com` — Right: `https://xxx.onrender.com/api` |
| CORS error in browser console | Set `CLIENT_URL` on Render to exact Vercel URL (no trailing slash) |
| Render deploy fails / crashes | Ensure **Start Command** is `npm start` and **Root Directory** is `server` |
| First request very slow | Render free tier wakes from sleep (~30–60s) |
| Works locally, fails in prod | Local uses Vite proxy `/api` → localhost; prod must use full Render HTTPS URL |
| SPA 404 on refresh | `client/vercel.json` rewrites non-file routes to `index.html` |

### Verify deployment

1. **Backend:** `https://YOUR-SERVICE.onrender.com/api/health` → JSON `{ "ok": true }`
2. **Backend root:** `https://YOUR-SERVICE.onrender.com/` → text `API is running`
3. **Frontend:** DevTools → Network → signup request URL must be `https://YOUR-SERVICE.onrender.com/api/auth/signup` (not `vercel.app/api/...`)
4. After changing Vercel env vars, trigger a **new deployment** (Redeploy), not just a cache refresh.
